==English==
===Etymology===
Anglo-Indian military slang, from Hindi ''jaldī'' ‘quickness’.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'ʤɪldi/

===Adverb===
'''jildy'''
# [[quickly]]
#:*'''1988''': ‘If you don’t drink that tea a bit '''jildy''' you’ll miss the bus.’ — Anthony Burgess, ''Any Old Iron''

